  "status_note": "Verified against ONS on 22 July 2026 and found unfit for publication. The 2016 value of 345,000 matches no ONS-published figure in any vintage checked (the discontinued LTIM series gives 249,000; first publication was 248,000). 2017 and 2018 likewise match nothing published. 2010, 2015 and 2019 mix vintages: they come from a different ONS series than their neighbours. 2021-2023 are superseded — the current ONS vintage gives 467,000, 891,000 and 848,000 against the 488,000, 764,000 and 872,000 held here, and the 2022 figure alone has moved by over 120,000. Only 2011-2014, 2024 and 2025 are confirmed correct. A series that silently mixes three vintages of the same statistic is the exact failure this project exists to correct. Awaiting a verified replacement structured as two explicitly labelled series: the current ONS new-approach series as primary, and the discontinued IPS/LTIM figures as clearly-marked history.",
